text:
Green, slender, leaf-embowered holly sprays  
Were wreath’d, most gracefu’, round her brows;  
I took her for a Scottish Muse,  
By that same token;  
And had I come to stay those reckless vows,  
Would soon have been broken.

source_text:
Green, slender, leaf-clad holly-boughs
Were twisted, gracefu’, round her brows;
I took her for some Scottish Muse,
By that same token;
And come to stop those reckless vows,
Would soon been broken.

text:
While Highlandmen loathe tools and taxes;
While moorland herds like good, fat braxies;
While terra firma, on her axis,
Diurnal turns;
Count on a friend, in faith and practice,
In Robert Burns.

source_text:
While Highlandmen hate tools an’ taxes;
While moorlan’s herds like guid, fat braxies;
While terra firma, on her axis,
Diurnal turns;
Count on a friend, in faith an’ practice,
In Robert Burns.

text:
The world’s wreck we share the burden;
The wrestle and the care of it;
Wi’ her I’ll gladly bear it,
And count my lot as heaven-blest.
She is a winsome, &c.

source_text:
The warld’s wrack we share o’t;
The warstle and the care o’t;
Wi’ her I’ll blythely bear it,
And think my lot divine.
She is a winsome, &c.

text:
It sets me aye as mad’s a hare;
So I can rhyme nor write nae mair;
But pennyworths again are fair,
When time’s expedient:
Meanwhile I am, respected Sir,
Your most obedient.

